1937, the eastern provinces of china grew economically under the leadership of chiang kai-shek and his kmt government, with marked economic expansion, industrialization and urbanization. shanghai became a truly cosmopolitan city, as one of the world's busiest ports, and the most prosperous city in east asia, home to millions of chinese and 60,000 foreigners from all corners of the globe. however, underlying problems throughout the vast country side, particularly the more inland parts of the country, such as civil unrest, famines and warlord conflict, still remained. japan established a puppet state under the name manchukuo in manchuria in 1931, and 